This article is a transcript of an interview between President Obama and ITAR-TASS/Rossiya TV. The interview took place in the Map Room of the White House on July 2, 2009. President Obama discusses his upcoming visit to Russia, the importance of Russian-American relations, and his goals for reducing nuclear stockpiles. He also talks about the challenges facing the United States, his personal heroes, and his family's experience living in the White House. President Obama expresses his respect for Russia and his desire to work together as equals. The interview ends with a gift exchange between the interviewer and President Obama.